dct_title_s: Map illustrating M. du Chaillu's routes in Equatorial Africa in 1864 & -65
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Inset: Sketch map of part of Western Africa. Shows M. du Chaillu's routes in red, and fixed astronomical observation positions. From: the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 36, (1866), pp. 64-76; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 vol.36 1866
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1866.
